Rules:
- Use "primary" for the main lesson/content source.
- Use "supporting" for visual references, companion PDFs, PPTX decks, and
  context files.
- Use "ignored" only for out-of-scope content.
- Binary supporting files such as PNG, JPG, PDF, and PPTX must use
  "expected_min_words": null.
- Textual primary/supporting files such as DOCX and Markdown must include an
  integer expected_min_words value.

